title: Artemis 1 cubesat nearing end of mission
summary: A cubesat launched as a secondary payload on Artemis 1 may end its operations at the end of the month unless it can get its propulsion system working.

title: Air Force to launch Link 16 tactical communications cubesat
summary: A U.S. Air Force Research Laboratory cubesat equipped with a Link 16 tactical communications radio will launch to low Earth orbit as early as June on the SpaceX Transporter 8 rideshare.

title: Satellite manufacturer LeoStella focused on defense market as commercial demand softens
summary: LeoStella, a manufacturer of small satellites, is pursuing U.S. defense sales amid a slowdown in production at its factory in Washington state near Seattle.

title: European space giants join forces for IRIS²
summary: Europe’s largest space companies have banded together to bid for a role in the European Union’s proposed multi-orbit connectivity constellation.
